      "updated_at": "2016-08-11T03:34:44Z",
      "body": "Consider these cases:\n- pseudo class name that contains `-`: `:last-child`\n- multiple pseudo classes: `.class-a:last-child:focus`\n\nHence my suggestion is:\n\n_CSS syntax Design:_\n\n```\n.class-a { color: blue; }\n.class-a:last-child:focus { color: red; }\n```\n\n_JS Bundle Format:_\n\n```\n{\n  \"class-a\": {\n    \"color\": \"blue\",\n    \"color:last-child:focus\": \"red\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nDevelopers can not directly specify pseudo class in property name like this: \n\n```\n.class-a { -focus-color: red; } \n```\n\nAnd specifying pseudo class in style prop is not allowed.\n\n@Jinjiang @cxfeng1 @MrRaindrop \n"
    },
