  "closed_at": "2016-12-23T12:43:36Z",
  "body": "**Summary:**\n\nWe can treat pseudo-class as normal class with every style prop name a pseudo-class prefix. For example: `.class-a:focus { color: red; }` equals to `.class-a { -focus-color: red; }`\n\n**Description:**\n\n_CSS syntax Design:_\n\n``` css\n.class-a { color: blue; }\n.class-a:focus { color: red; } /* pseudo-class */\n.class-a { -focus-color: red; } /* same effect */\n```\n\n_JS Bundle Format:_\n\n``` javascript\n{\n  \"class-a\": {\n    \"color\": \"blue\",\n    \"-focus-color\": \"red\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n_Renderer Implementation:_\n\nSupport `color` style and `-focus-color` when user tap on it. The interaction will not fire any JS task so it's faster than event.\n"
